# BT Module — Behavior Tree Sample Nodes

## Module Purpose and Responsibilities

The BT module (`Code/PigeonLib/BT/`) provides a set of **reference sample nodes** built on top of the third-party [BehaviorTree.CPP v3](https://github.com/BehaviorTreeCPP/BehaviorTree.CPP) library. These nodes serve as concrete usage examples for the three primary node execution styles supported by BehaviorTree.CPP:

- **Synchronous action nodes** (`BT::SyncActionNode`) — complete in one tick.
- **Asynchronous action nodes** (`BT::AsyncActionNode`) — run on a background thread; `tick()` blocks until done.
- **Stateful action nodes** (`BT::StatefulActionNode`) — explicitly manage start, running, and halted states across ticks.

The module is **not compiled into PigeonLib**. Its `CMakeLists.txt` is intentionally disabled (filename prefixed with `_`), and no glob pattern in `Code/PigeonLib/CMakeLists.txt` includes the `BT/` subtree. The sample nodes exist as integration guidance and are designed to be compiled as standalone static or shared (plugin) libraries when BehaviorTree.CPP is linked.

There are no test files in `Code/UT/` that exercise these sample nodes. The BehaviorTree.CPP library itself is also not listed as a CMake FetchContent dependency in the top-level `CMakeLists.txt`.

---

## Dependencies

| Dependency | Role |
|---|---|
| `behaviortree_cpp_v3/behavior_tree.h` | Core node hierarchy, status enum, port system, string conversion utilities |
| `behaviortree_cpp_v3/bt_factory.h` | `BT::BehaviorTreeFactory` — runtime node registration and tree construction |

The BT module has **no dependency on any other PigeonLib module** (no ECS, no renderer, no UI, no events). It is entirely self-contained relative to the engine.

---

## Node Status Values

All nodes return `BT::NodeStatus`, an enum defined by BehaviorTree.CPP with three values:

| Value | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `NodeStatus::SUCCESS` | The node completed its task successfully. |
| `NodeStatus::FAILURE` | The node was unable to complete its task. |
| `NodeStatus::RUNNING` | The node has started its task but has not yet finished (used by async and stateful nodes). |

---

## Node Hierarchy

### Base Types (from BehaviorTree.CPP v3)

| Base Class | Execution Model |
|---|---|
| `BT::SyncActionNode` | Subclass for single-tick actions; override `tick()`. The constructor must accept `(const std::string& name, const BT::NodeConfiguration& config)`. |
| `BT::AsyncActionNode` | Subclass for threaded actions; `tick()` blocks in a background thread. Override both `tick()` and `halt()`. A `_halt_requested` atomic flag is used to cooperatively interrupt execution. |
| `BT::StatefulActionNode` | Subclass for multi-tick actions that manage their own phase; override `onStart()`, `onRunning()`, and `onHalted()`. |

### Derived Node Types (Defined in This Module)

All concrete node classes are in `Code/PigeonLib/BT/sample_nodes/`.

