## Public Types and Classes

### `dummy_nodes.h` / `dummy_nodes.cpp` — namespace `DummyNodes`

#### Free Functions

```cpp
BT::NodeStatus CheckBattery();
BT::NodeStatus CheckTemperature();
BT::NodeStatus SayHello();
BT::NodeStatus SaySomethingSimple(BT::TreeNode& self);
```

- `CheckBattery()` — Prints `"[ Battery: OK ]"` to stdout; always returns `SUCCESS`. Used as a simple condition node registered via `registerSimpleCondition`.
- `CheckTemperature()` — Prints `"[ Temperature: OK ]"` to stdout; always returns `SUCCESS`.
- `SayHello()` — Prints `"Robot says: Hello World"` to stdout; always returns `SUCCESS`.
- `SaySomethingSimple(BT::TreeNode& self)` — Reads the `"message"` input port from `self`; prints it to stdout; throws `BT::RuntimeError` if the port is missing. Returns `SUCCESS`. Used with `registerSimpleAction` (signature compatible with `SimpleActionNode` registration).

#### `GripperInterface`

```cpp
class GripperInterface
{
public:
    GripperInterface();
    BT::NodeStatus open();
    BT::NodeStatus close();
private:
    bool _opened;
};
```

- A plain C++ object (not a `TreeNode` subclass) whose member functions are registered as simple action callbacks via `std::bind`.
- `open()` — Sets `_opened = true`; prints to stdout; returns `SUCCESS`.
- `close()` — Sets `_opened = false`; prints to stdout; returns `SUCCESS`.
- A static singleton instance (`grip_singleton`) is created inside `RegisterNodes()` and bound to the factory.

#### `ApproachObject` — `BT::SyncActionNode`

```cpp
class ApproachObject : public BT::SyncActionNode
{
public:
    ApproachObject(const std::string& name);
    NodeStatus tick() override;
};
```

- Constructor takes only `name`; passes `{}` (empty `NodeConfiguration`) to the base class — this node declares **no ports**.
- `tick()` — Prints the node's name to stdout; always returns `SUCCESS`.

#### `SaySomething` — `BT::SyncActionNode`

```cpp
class SaySomething : public BT::SyncActionNode
{
public:
    SaySomething(const std::string& name, const BT::NodeConfiguration& config);
    NodeStatus tick() override;
    static BT::PortsList providedPorts();
};
```

- Declares one input port: `BT::InputPort<std::string>("message")`.
- `tick()` — Reads `"message"` via `getInput<std::string>("message")`; prints it; throws `BT::RuntimeError` if absent. Returns `SUCCESS`.
- `providedPorts()` must be `static` — BehaviorTree.CPP calls it at registration time to build the port manifest.

#### `SleepNode` — `BT::StatefulActionNode`

```cpp
class SleepNode : public BT::StatefulActionNode
{
public:
    SleepNode(const std::string& name, const BT::NodeConfiguration& config);
    static BT::PortsList providedPorts();
    NodeStatus onStart() override;
    NodeStatus onRunning() override;
    void onHalted() override;
private:
    std::chrono::system_clock::time_point deadline_;
};
```

- Declares one input port: `BT::InputPort<int>("msec")`.
- `onStart()` — Reads `"msec"`. If `msec <= 0`, returns `SUCCESS` immediately (no RUNNING state needed). Otherwise, computes `deadline_ = now + msec milliseconds` and returns `RUNNING`.
- `onRunning()` — Called on every subsequent tick while in RUNNING state. Returns `SUCCESS` once `now >= deadline_`; otherwise returns `RUNNING`.
- `onHalted()` — Called when the tree interrupts this node. Prints `"SleepNode interrupted"` to stdout. No internal state to reset.

#### `RegisterNodes` (inline)

```cpp
inline void DummyNodes::RegisterNodes(BT::BehaviorTreeFactory& factory);
```

Registers all `DummyNodes` with the factory under the following names:

| Registered Name | Kind | Implementation |
|---|---|---|
| `"CheckBattery"` | SimpleCondition | `CheckBattery` function |
| `"CheckTemperature"` | SimpleCondition | `CheckTemperature` function |
| `"SayHello"` | SimpleAction | `SayHello` function |
| `"OpenGripper"` | SimpleAction | `GripperInterface::open` (bound to static singleton) |
| `"CloseGripper"` | SimpleAction | `GripperInterface::close` (bound to static singleton) |
| `"ApproachObject"` | NodeType (`ApproachObject`) | via `registerNodeType<ApproachObject>` |
| `"SaySomething"` | NodeType (`SaySomething`) | via `registerNodeType<SaySomething>` |

`BT_REGISTER_NODES(factory)` at the top of `dummy_nodes.cpp` calls `DummyNodes::RegisterNodes(factory)` — this is the plugin entry point used when this file is compiled as a shared library.

