### `movebase_node.h` / `movebase_node.cpp`

#### `Pose2D` (custom struct)

```cpp
struct Pose2D
{
    double x, y, theta;
};
```

A plain 2D pose with position and heading. Defined outside any namespace.

#### `BT::convertFromString<Pose2D>` (template specialization)

```cpp
namespace BT {
    template <> inline
    Pose2D convertFromString(StringView key);
}
```

Enables automatic string-to-`Pose2D` conversion when a tree node calls `getInput<Pose2D>(...)`. The expected format is three semicolon-separated real numbers (e.g., `"1.0;2.5;0.785"`). Throws `BT::RuntimeError` if the string does not contain exactly three parts.

#### `MoveBaseAction` — `BT::AsyncActionNode`

```cpp
class MoveBaseAction : public BT::AsyncActionNode
{
public:
    MoveBaseAction(const std::string& name, const BT::NodeConfiguration& config);
    static BT::PortsList providedPorts();
    BT::NodeStatus tick() override;
    virtual void halt() override;
private:
    std::atomic_bool _halt_requested;
};
```

- Declares one input port: `BT::InputPort<Pose2D>("goal")`.
- `tick()` — Reads `"goal"` via `getInput<Pose2D>`; throws `BT::RuntimeError` if absent. Stores `_halt_requested = false`, then loops 25 iterations of 10 ms sleeps (~250 ms total), checking `_halt_requested` each iteration. Returns `FAILURE` if halted early; `SUCCESS` otherwise.
- `halt()` — Sets `_halt_requested = true` atomically. Called from the BT infrastructure to interrupt an in-flight `tick()`.

`BT_REGISTER_NODES(factory)` in `movebase_node.cpp` registers `MoveBaseAction` under the name `"MoveBase"`.

